In 
computer graphics, Boundary fill, or Boundary-fill is an algorithm used to fill an area with a specified color. The algorithm works by filling an area with a specified color until the specified boundary color is encoutered. It is similar to the 







Flood fill






 algorithm.


The algorithm




The algorithm works by starting in a specified point (x,y), filling that point with the specified fill color if it is not a boundary and recursively continuing with the 4 or eight closest neighbours. The example below uses the 4 closest neighbours.




void boundaryFill(int x, int y, int fill, int boundary) { 
int current; 
current = getPixel(x, y); 
if ((current != boundary) && (current != fill)) { 
setColor(fill); 
setPixel(x, y); 
boundaryFill(x+1, y, fill, boundary); 
boundaryFill(x-1, y, fill, boundary); 
boundaryFill(x, y+1, fill, boundary); 
boundaryFill(x, y-1, fill, boundary); 
} 
}





Other Uses




The Boundary fill algorithm can also be used in games like 









SameGame








, in which same color adjacent blocks must be destroyed.




